---
const installGuideUrl =
  "https://github.com/hiep1987/sniptex/blob/main/docs/install-guide.md";
---

<section id="install" class="border-b border-ink-200 bg-ink-50 py-16 sm:py-20 dark:border-ink-800 dark:bg-ink-900">
  <div class="container-wide">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink-950 sm:text-4xl dark:text-white">
        First-launch checklist
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300">
        Both Mac and Windows ship unsigned-by-identity (no Apple Developer
        cert yet — fund the $99/yr via <a href="#donate" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline dark:text-blue-400">donations</a>).
        You'll see one OS dialog the first time.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-10 grid max-w-4xl gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <article class="rounded-xl border border-ink-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-ink-700 dark:bg-ink-950">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-950 dark:text-white">macOS</h3>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-200">
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">1.</span> Open the DMG and drag
            <strong>SnipTeX.app</strong> onto the Applications shortcut.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">2.</span> On <strong>macOS 12–14</strong>:
            right-click <strong>SnipTeX.app</strong> → <em>Open</em>, then
            click <em>Open</em> in the dialog.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">3.</span> On <strong>macOS 15 (Sequoia)</strong>:
            double-click once, dismiss the warning, then open
            <em>System Settings → Privacy &amp; Security</em> and click
            <strong>Open Anyway</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">4.</span> If you see <em>"App is damaged"</em>:
            <div class="code-block mt-2">
              <code>xattr -cr /Applications/SnipTeX.app</code>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">5.</span> Grant Accessibility
            permission when prompted (needed for the global hotkey).
          </li>
        </ol>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-xl border border-ink-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-ink-700 dark:bg-ink-950">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-950 dark:text-white">Windows</h3>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-200">
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">1.</span> Double-click the MSI.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">2.</span> SmartScreen shows
            <em>"Windows protected your PC"</em>. Click
            <strong>More info → Run anyway</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">3.</span> If Smart App Control (Win 11
            22H2+) blocks the MSI silently, switch it off temporarily under
            <em>Settings → Windows Security → App &amp; browser control</em>.
            <span class="block mt-1 text-xs text-ink-500 dark:text-ink-400">
              Heads-up: Smart App Control is one-way. Once off, can't be re-enabled without a Windows reinstall.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">4.</span> Follow the installer prompts.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium">5.</span> Launch from Start Menu →
            <em>"SnipTeX"</em>. Default hotkey:
            <code class="rounded bg-ink-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-xs dark:bg-ink-800">Ctrl+Shift+M</code>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-center text-sm text-ink-500 dark:text-ink-400">
      Full troubleshooting matrix lives in the
      <a href={installGuideUrl} class="text-blue-600 hover:underline dark:text-blue-400">
        install guide on GitHub
      </a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
